  "prompt": "Is romantic love real love?",
  "response": "The concept of \"real love\" can be quite subjective and varies significantly across cultures, philosophies, and individual beliefs. Romantic love is one form of love, typically characterized by emotional attachment, attraction, intimacy, and passion between individuals. Whether or not this qualifies as \"real love\" largely depends on one's definition of love.\n\nSome argue that romantic love is indeed real love because it involves genuine emotional bonds and mutual care between partners. It often includes elements of companionship, shared values, and personal growth, which are seen as foundational attributes of any authentic loving relationship.\n\nOthers might suggest that romantic love is just one part of a broader spectrum of love, which might also include familial love, platonic love, self-love, and unconditional love. In these views, true or enduring love may go beyond the passionate and often fleeting nature of romantic attraction to encompass deeper commitment, understanding, and acceptance.\n\nUltimately, whether romantic love is considered real love is a matter of personal interpretation. Each individual may have different criteria for what constitutes real love based on their own values, experiences, and beliefs.",
